class Solution {
    public String reverseWords(String s) {
        s = s.trim();
        String[] words = s.split("\\s+");
        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();
        for (int i = words.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            result.append(words[i]);
            if (i > 0) {
                result.append(" ");
            }
        }
        return result.toString();
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution efficiently removes leading and trailing spaces, splits the string into words, and reverses their order. It uses a StringBuilder to minimize string concatenations, resulting in a linear time complexity. The space complexity is also linear due to the storage of the words array and the result StringBuilder. 
